            "body": "<p>Scanner use to get token(Split string by some deliminator, default is space) of string for processing.<\/p>\n\n<p>If you change next() method with nextLine() then it will return entire line without token.<\/p>\n\n<p>Try.<\/p>\n\n<p>userInput = Menu.menuScanner.nextLine();\n count0 = userInput.length();\n System.out.println(\"Your string is: \" + count0 + \" characters long.\");<\/p>\n\n<p>OR<\/p>\n\n<p>Scanner sc = Menu.menuScanner.useDelimiter(\"\\n\");\nuserInput = Menu.menuScanner.next();\ncount0 = userInput.length();\nSystem.out.println(\"Your string is: \" + count0 + \" characters long.\");<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 37772834,
            "question_id": 37772668
        },
